{
  "text": "Derangement of mineral metabolism is regarded as the leading factor responsible for cardiac valve calcification. The association between mineral metabolism and cardiac valve calcification has been extensively evaluated in ESRD patients but seldom in patients with CKD-ND [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
